34—38. Augustus entered Alexandria, which had been evacuated by the forces of Antony in the autumn of B.C. 30. F isteen years, therefore (three lustres) had passed when the victories of the young Neroes were won. Scaliger notes that there was the same interval between the death of Caesar and the entry into Alexandria (only to be made out, however, by including both years, 44, 30), and, indeed, interprets the passage of this coincidence.
